name: Trireme Armor
flavorProject: We do not yet have facilities capable of creating armor that can withstand a Primordial attack. But we have access to war triremes

name: Siren Armor
flavorProject: Experimentation leads us to suspect that the hardened AE-siren shells will make a great stop-gap defensive solution

name: Smelted Gear
flavorProject: The bronze statues and reliefs of our gods and heroes, now gone and lost forever, retain a whif of their resolve and power
requirements: Specialized Trireme Weapons and either: Advanced Support Equipment OR Hekaton Autopsy

name: Basic Support Equipment
flavorProject: The Triskelion Junction is more malleable than we first thought. We may be able to tinker with the Antikratos Helms to spur specific reactions

name: Advanced Support Equipment
flavorProject: It is time to put what we have learned from our dealings withe Labyrinthauros into practice

name: Trireme Weapons
flavorProject: Conventional mortal-scale weapons cannot penetrate the Primordials' AT fields. We need to think bigger

name: Advanced Trireme Weapons
flavorProject: We need to hit harder and faster, Poseidon's bounty should serve us well

name: Specialized Trireme Weapons
flavorProject: State of the art improvised weaponry and our first foray into relief remelting
requirements: Advanced Trireme Weapons and either: Teleresuscitation OR Trireme Reach Weapons

name: Trireme Ranged Weapons
flavorProject: Close-quarters combat with Primordials continues to carry a high mortality rate for the Titans, maybe we could put some of that war trireme equipment to better use

name: Trireme Reach Weapons
flavorProject: As reports of larger and more aggressive Primordials keep coming in, we need to think of ways to hold them at arm's length

name: Hekaton Sighting
flavorProject: The apex predator of the Cretan countryside. It is said to bear the mark of the Labyrinth on its massive prime arms

name: Hekaton Autopsy
flavorProject: We've been able to recover a mostly intact Hekaton carcass. The philosophers of the Last Academy think that by studying it we may find its weakness

name: Hekaton Live Study
flavorProject: A scout team has been following a Hekaton for a fortnight. The beast does not tire, sleep, or eat - though it tries to imitate the latter. It adorns itself with crude 'jewelry', which suggests some form of intelligence

name: Labyrinthauros Sighting
flavorProject: Mechanical sentry, purportedly of Daedalus's design. It appears without warning and vanishes without a trace, suggesting some kind of supernatural force at work

name: Labyrinthauros Autopsy
flavorProject: The Argo Works artificers managed to break this thing apart. It's no automaton. Behind the rusted machinery, an amorphous body hides, not unlike a snail. The priests believe it's some kind of worm

name: Labyrinthauros Live Study
flavorProject: The creature does not travel through the earthly realm, nor does it adhere to the laws of the gods. It can materialize and dematerialize, seemingly at will, using some kind of portal reminiscent of the maze pattern. Does the Labyrinth extend to the unseen world?

name: Temenos Sighting
flavorProject: An unholy union of stone and flesh, this gargantuan Primordial it the Truth of the Labyrinth made manifest
requirements: Temenos LVL 1 Battle and either: Labyrinthauros Live Study OR Hekaton Live Study

name: Pursuer Sighting
flavorProject: Why does it hunt us so? Where it take the prisoners? And why does it laugh?

name: Temenos Armor
flavorProject: Temenos's mazeflesh is some kind of coral composite, harder than stone. It'll do

name: Temenos Weapons
flavorProject: With the proper emotional stimulation, Temenos's remains still contract and expand. We can weaponize this

name: Lakonian Support Equipment
flavorProject: Thanks to reconnaissance, we know what we'll be up against. The Last Academy has prepared some equipment that will extend Titan survivability

name: Temenos Advanced Gear
flavorProject: As we tinker with the transformative properties of Temenos's flesh, new, more intricate weapon designs become available

name: Temenos Support Equipment
flavorProject: The Last Academy scholars have devised plans for utility equipment employing more intricate maze designs

name: Relief Gear
flavorProject: The Chimera's temple shell has some peculiar properties. There may be some latent divine power lingering there. Power we could harness

name: Metal Weapons
flavorProject: Argo Works are sure they can reverse-engineer the Spartan smelting process

name: Experimental Gear
flavorProject: Our Helot allies have provided us with plans for Leleges-Spartan hybrid weapons

name: Spartan Weapons
flavorProject: Palamedes of the Last Academy has blended Titan, mortal, and Primordial designs and came up with some interesting offensive and defensive solutions

name: Spartan Advanced Weapons
flavorProject: Hidden within the Helot plans were the seeds for the next generation Cyclonus weapons

name: War Support Equipment
flavorProject: New Antikratos Helm designs and rough terrain footwear will greatly increase the Titans' mobility

name: Cyclopean Gear
flavorProject: Our Cyclopean allies have provided us with plans for some intricate designs we can repurpose for combat

name: Cyclopean Advanced Gear
flavorProject: Though war goes against the Cyclopes basic principles, they do possess some devastating heavy-duty gear

name: Cyclonus Sighting
flavorProject: The Cyclonus are Cyclopes conditioned into merciless killing machines. We need to ensure the Triskelion Junction doesn't have an averse effect on our Titans

name: Cyclonus Autopsy
flavorProject: On close inspection, a body of a Cyclonus shows signs of severe mutilation and torture conditioning. Some of the augmentations go all the way to the central nervous system

name: Cyclonus Live Study
flavorProject: When left to its own devices, a Cyclonus shows a degree of intelligence and autonomy. There are signs the Nietzschean's conditioning is only temporary

name: Chimera Metastasios Sighting
flavorProject: A colossal heap of condensed ambrosia, dead monster tissue, and temple ruins. The Chimera shows no signs of intelligence, though, thanks to its relief shell, it has a remarkable camouflage ability

name: Chimera Metastasios Autopsy
flavorProject: The Chimera leaves a faint shadow in the Triskelion, which has our scholars convinced the ambrosia creates some sort of neural network. The larger the ambrosia mass, the more activity we register

name: Chimera Metastasios Live Study
flavorProject: The Chimera is driven by two instincts: to consume living matter and to merge with other Chimeras. The largest specimen exhibit basic animal intelligence. Is the Chimera evolving into something different?

name: Nietzschean Meeting Study
flavorProject: The Nietzschean man and the Nietzschean monster share the same mind, but seem to operate independently. What exactly is the connection here?
requirements: Cyclonus Live Study OR Chimera Metastasios Live Study

name: Bronze Lair
flavorProject: Nature - or some other malevalent force - has bred this creature with a singular purpose. To hunt Titans. The cryptex found inside seems to work in an eerily similar way to the Triskelion Junction

name: Burden Sighting
flavorProject: The black rock of Ephyra. The bane of Sisyphus. It does not allow us to ascend

name: Nietzschean Weapons
flavorProject: In death, the Nietzschean will serve one last purpose

name: Nietzschean Reach Weapons
flavorProject: The Nietzschean abhored ranged weapons. Forge them to spite him

name: Nietzschean Armor
flavorProject: What is left of the Nietzschean's Shadow will become your shield

name: Temporal Support Equipment
flavorProject: Delphi is stuck in some kind of temporal anomaly. Combating its effects is of top priority

name: Delphian Siren Armor
flavorProject: Before the Eschaton, the Sirens were not the viscious beasts they are now. This armor is proof

name: Delphian Siren Weapons
flavorProject: Some of these weapons were fashioned from Siren shells, others come from pre-Eschaton Siren caches

name: Advanced Transforming Weapons
flavorProject: Palamedian advanced transforming weaponry is becoming a necessity
requirements: and either: Icarian Harpy Sighting OR Hypertime Oracle Sighting

name: Atemporal Support Equipment
flavorProject: The Last Academy needs to find advanced solutions against the more esoteric temporal effects of the Delphian Anomaly

name: Black Ice Armor
flavorProject: Ambrosia-tainted ice has remarkable anti-entropy properties

name: Argoline Transforming Weapons
flavorProject: State of the art anti-Primordial weaponry. The best mortals have to offer

name: Cryptex Technology
flavorProject: Our study of the Repurposed Cryptex has finally yielded results. We can replicate that design

name: Helios Fanatics Equipment
flavorProject: This is the gear of the Hyperborean zealots who embraced Helios's toxic love

name: Helios Fanatics Light Weapons
flavorProject: Helios bestowed many gifts onto His chosen, weapon harnessing light among them

name: Apostate Armor
flavorProject: This armor was worn by those Hyperboreans who rejected Helios's incinerating love

name: Apostate Weapons
flavorProject: Denied the light, the Hyperborean Apostates thrived in the shade

name: Hypertime Oracle Sighting
flavorProject: Even observing the Hypertime Oracle has a profound impact on the observer
requirements: and either: Hypertime Oracle LVL 2 Battle OR gain +1 Paradox

name: Hypertime Oracle Autopsy
flavorProject: The autopsy of the Oracle has revealed some disturbing truths: this Primordial was a mortal once

name: Hypertime Oracle Live Study
flavorProject: The Oracle uses the Delphi time loop to prune timelines and evolve

name: Icarian Harpy Sighting
flavorProject: Its adaptation abilities are far beyond anything in Hellas
requirements: Fate Converter and either: Icarian Harpy LVL 2 Battle OR gain +1 Paradox

name: Icarian Harpy Autopsy
flavorProject: A product of forced evolution, the Icarian Harpy is technically a Primordial-mortal hybrid

name: Icarian Harpy Live Study
flavorProject: The Harpy lives to evolve and evolves to become a perfect species

name: Sun Descendant Sighting
flavorProject: We need to find a way to shield the Titans from the pitiless Sun

name: Sun Descendant Partial Autopsy
flavorProject: The partial autopsy on the Primordial's fragment reveals troubling divine connection

name: Sun Descendant Live Study
flavorProject: The Primordial descends from a black spot near the Sun. Helios's Domain

name: Monomythological Support
flavorProject: Stuff of legends. Yet know that those legends failed

name: Burden Autopsy
flavorProject: Save for ambrosia, the Burden is empty and incredibly light
requirements: Burden Hardest to Bear Battle Victory

name: Cinder Weapons
flavorProject: From the cinders of the old world, we will make a better one

name: Cinder Ranged Weapons
flavorProject: Weapons capable of chasing the Sun across the horizon

name: Cinder Armor
flavorProject: Once the source of light was known, it stopped providing warmth

name: Cinder Support
flavorProject: What knowledge we could gleam from the lies of light and the truths of aid

name: Imperial Deprived Armorer
flavorProject: Even on their back foot, the Empire was always the aggressor

name: Imperial Deprived Outfitter
flavorProject: In the past, the Empire employed the Deprived in warfare

name: Imperial Deprived Stockpile
flavorProject: The Empire has developed many wonderous technologies to exploit its citizens

name: Old Irem Dig
flavorProject: Who inhabited Old Irem, and when?

name: Old Irem Excavation
flavorProject: The Empire erases their history well, but evidence suggests the Deprived once rose against it, wielding the arms of Old Irem
requirements: Imperial Deprived Outfitter and either Cloud Support Fleet OR Old Irem Dig

name: Old Irem Composite Shop
flavorProject: Of Old Irem culture, next to nothing remains. Yet their crooked spires have inspired this research

name: Djinn Fundhoard
flavorProject: The Deprived have devised many ways of fighting injustice and climbing the illusory ladder

name: Curse Shapers
flavorProject: The Aristotelians have "liberated" many a treasury but had no use for these indivisible tools of the system they so desired

name: Tekne Restorers
flavorProject: This tekne could have changed the world, and they hid it. Not viable economically, they said. Disruptive

name: Midascore Sighting
flavorProject: Severely maligned, it spreads the Midas Touch and other, more exotic curses

name: Midascore Autopsy
flavorProject: The autopsy shows the Midascore has been made a slave of the Empire via a carefully foged chain of obligations

name: Midascore Live Study
flavorProject: It lives to multiply wealth, which is ironic, for it devalues all it touches. The contradiction drives it mad

name: Demidjinn Sighting
flavorProject: Its driven to mortal settlements. It drowns them in a deluge of wishes, until nothing remains

name: Demidjinn Autopsy
flavorProject: In essence, these are two beings forcibly conjoined, though the specificities of the process elude our scholars

name: Demidjinn Live Study
flavorProject: The Demidjinn's wishes are real, in as much as they influence the waking world. The energy needed is atronomical. Where do they draw it from?

name: Babelian Lunacy Sighting
flavorProject: Come, let us build ourselves a city and a tower with its top in the heavens, and a staircase anyone could climb
requirements: Grassroots Projects and either Midascore Live Study OR Demidjinn Live Study

name: Grassroot Projects
flavorProject: On the stele, the important part was left out. But we finally see it

name: Insolvency Bulwark
flavorProject: After careful analysis, the stele's true purpose might have been revealed: to preserve against, not destroy

name: Highrise Projects
flavorProject: Studying the Pandoran Phos stele has yielded many useful horrors. Tread lightly

name: Dahaka Sighting
flavorProject: Those who turn from their God and sow to please their sinful nature will reap destruction and despair

name: Dahaka Autopsy
errata: Original card says "Still Life Battle Victory", which does not exist
flavorProject: A curse made manifest. Empty, like its threats and promises, it leaves one final clue: the divine nature of its puppet master

name: Cryptex Technology
flavorProject: Our study of the Repurposed Cryptex has finally yielded results. We can replicate that design

name: Monomythological Support
flavorProject: Stuff of legends. Yet know that those legends failed

name: Babelian Armor
flavorProject: Deep blood-stone from the bowels of the Lunacy

name: Babelian Weapons
flavorProject: The oldest reclaimed part of the tower show a surprising connection to Selene

name: Babelian Ranged Weapons
flavorProject: Forged in a place where greeds met the sky

name: Babelian Support
flavorProject: Natural, manufactured, stolen--light is light

name: Abyss Armor
flavorProject: Crude but effective diving gear

name: Abyss Weapons
flavorProject: Sharpened within the deepest trenches

name: Abyss Support
flavorProject: The only hope in the abyss is the one you bring along with you

name: Vanguard Gear
flavorProject: Your academicians are having trouble dating these disparate Silver Ones relics

name: Cycladean Protectorate
flavorProject: The Rhodian curatos swear by the authenticity of these Silver Ones relics

name: Followers of Areté Gear
flavorProject: You would be forgiven for thinking these Silver Ones artifacts were crafted by one of the Bronze Peoples. Curious

name: Atlantean Armor
flavorProject: The Shipbreakers were able to salvage most of these early Silver Ones artifacts

name: Atlantean Weapons
flavorProject: Much was lost with the fall of Atlantis, but what you can find, you can repurpose

name: Atlantean Support
flavorProject: The Atlanteans were decades, maybe a century ahead of other mortal peoples. And yet their society failed...

name: Dragon of Phobos Sighting
flavorProject: The Dragon is oddly timid and keeps to the dark--but the light of distant pearls draws it out

name: Dragon of Phobos Autopsy
flavorProject: Its whole body is full of amygdalas. Prolonged exposure to them elicits strong anxiety

name: Dragon of Phobos Live Study
flavorProject: It lives in the deepest trenches, on a diet of fear and aether

name: Meduketos Sighting
flavorProject: It skitters across the seabed, prefering to stay within the obscuring vapors of the black smoke vents

name: Meduketos Autopsy
flavorProject: Though possessing many eyes, it is effectively blind, relying on echolocation and heatsense

name: Meduketos Live Study
flavorProject: Thanks to its heat generation and retention properties, the Meduketos could surivve the icy cold voids of Kokytos itself

name: Silvered Weapons
flavorProject: By applying a current to the orichalcum chunks, the academicians were able to change their matter state

name: Silvered Armor
flavorProject: Liquid Orichalcum sticks to organic surfaces

name: Silvered Support
flavorProject: Orichalcum seems to be an inert form of the compound

name: Ur-Fleece Sighting
flavorProject: It comes when the Truth Machine is spun; it does not want us to know something
requirements: Calculate Statistical Certainty AND EITHER Dragon of Phobos Live Study OR Meduketos Live Study

name: Titan X Sighting
flavorProject: There is no question about it, this Titan is piloted. Who stalks you?

name: Titan X Investigation
errata: Original card says "Titan X Battle Victory"
flavorProject: The tekne and cryptex are unmistakably Nemesistech, though more advanced than you have thus far seen

name: Cryptex Technology
flavorProject: Our study of the Repurposed Cryptex has finally yielded results. We can replicate that design

name: Monomythological Support
flavorProject: Stuff of legends. Yet know that those legends failed
